content: What all good adventures should be....a mix of puzzles ranging from easy to difficult, whilst allowing a bit of nonlinear exploration. Well designed and intriguing enough to keep the player coming back to see what's been missed...and believe me you will kick yourself every time you discover something you didn't see first time. If patience isn't your strong point.... buy this anyway as it's worth every cent.
Some of the puzzles are very difficult to solve and some clues very hard to find. There are no hints available in the game.
Disappointed! Was so excited to play this game but it kept freezing everytime I clicked in an object.

15 hours of fantastic gameplay. Mostly great graphics, great soundtrack, and most importantly, challenging but entertaining puzzles. Quite often you have no unsolved puzzles (or so you think), no items and no idea what to do next. But explore, read, look for subtle hints from everywhere and everything... And you'll always get forward. Well, most of the time, had to look up answers online a couple of times. üòÅ As a game, on par with The Rooms, if not better. Definitely harder. Deserves more attn.

There are few puzzles that are broken in my game. I am sure that I have solved them in a correct way but the game is not doing its thing to proceed any further. I had to watch walkthrough if I am correct and in walkthrough the player did things in the same way than I did. So I cannot play the game to an end.
Love, love, love this game.
Sadly keeps freezing & can't get past the intro üòï

*Update* Someone else mentioned the blue light filter in the comments, and that solved my issues! If it won't work, check for a screen dimmer or blue light filter. Definitely 5 star game! I LOVE this game so far, but most of the time, it doesn't work for me. The app opens but is completely unresponsive to my touch. I really, really want to play more because the puzzles are fabulous and the graphics are gorgeous, but I can't get it to work! If you fix this, I'll definitely update to 5 stars.

Nice game almost like the house of Da Vinci or the rooms. However, this do not have a proper ending so I ended up wandering around for 2 hours frustrated. Hopefully you will put up something to tell people that there is an extra or it is the end. It is too confusing.
Great graphics and game, but keeps crashing. Had to uninstall, reinstall & start the game over - twice - and now it's just crashed again!
despite arranging the symbols on the ceiling correctly the bookcase does not move. is this a system fault?
Fun game but locks up often.
ü§ò
Game is great but keeps crashing!! I can't get past puzzle on the wall by the lab. The stone ring
Nerve-wracking, addictive, and humbling. Love it!
very good and interesting story line. keeps you coming back for more!
Very intriguing storyline. Love the puzzles. I don't think I could have finished without the walkthrough.
Very good keeps you on your toes
Very good game üëç

My issues were UI and hints. The button for notes is at the bottom right, but notes are stored at the top. This means continual accidental taps of Settings button at the top are irritating. This game is complex and the notes are vague so sometimes you keep searching and can't figure out how to move forward. I finally used a walkthrough cuz the in-game hint options didn't work right. Some people will not like this fact. I loved the storyline and will replay. Suggest making player the niece.
Superb quality game in every single ways
Whats the point..? Paid for a pain in the head and utube walk through solutions to going nowhere puzzles. Two star max.
Nice and long game, not a lot of hints, worth it.
Beautiful graphics and I'm sure it would be a great game if it didn't constantly crash, unless I've missed something. Update ... I did miss something.
Google Play Games spyware added in the latest release. Uninstalled.
Love this game! Very entertaining, and makes you think! Wish these guys made more games!!!! Also, started to play again on Christmas Eve, was thrilled to see the Christmas decor added to the game!

Great visuals and detail. Good level of challenge to solve each mystery. I like this game because it is not like others that just present you with 50 or 100 variations of sliding puzzles. Update: And now with Christmas decorations! How cool is that?
It is only playable on my Note 20 ultra, tested on Galaxy Fold z2 and Oppo find x2 The buttons won't respond to touches.

This was one of the hardest but well made puzzle games i have ever played in this app store. hands down a MUST PLAY kind of game. the graphics was great, puzzles were challenging, and the story line with the jornals were enjoyable. i really liked the ending. no spoilers. lol. I am recommending this game to so many ppl.
Best Game EVER!!! Gotta Have MORE like it!!!

With a cynical sneer I clicked 'Purchase' on yet another slight variation of the same old Room Escape we seem doomed to play over and over - it's not the room that traps us, but the genre - and felt my sneer replaced by wide-eyed wonder. Underpinning fantastic locations and spectacular graphics is the fundamental truth that sets TEoA on a pinnacle all its own: this is no Room Escape - you are never trapped by anything but curiosity. Thank you for crafting a 'Room Escape Game' to set us free!
I love these puzzle games! üòä
Very smooth playing game, reminds me of the good old myst
I am enjoying the game. Very well done. It was definitely worth the cost.

Can not play. Stucked at the welcome screen with 3 new game buttons. That was all. I could do nothing. Fortunately, the refund button works like a charm. üòÜ If this issue is solved, I'll buy it again My device: Samsung S20 Ultra
Great mysterious puzzle game
Great puzzle game! Challenging, so it lasts longer
I was looking for a Room style game and am very happy to say I found one. Great game.
no directions sometimes not logical
This is a really good game and worth the cost. It makes you think and is challenging too, just the game I was looking for. It's similar to Myst, which I also like.
This game is brilliant. It's better than The Room, and that's a great game.
Thumbs up!
I can't even drag the items from the inventory to open the gate from start 1. I am just literally stuck from the very start. I have wasted my money on buying this game.

Good overall but it's quite dark, even on max brightness the details of rooms are hard to pick out. I prefer to play without hints but illumination of targets does help Controls are a bit slow compare to other games, not brutal but irksome.

Oh My Wow. Absolutely love this game! A good challenge but no parts that seem like a reach. The story being told through notes is great although I wish we would see a wrap up of what happens with the person you are playing, feels like the intro part was lost.

Similar toThe Room, but lacking direction, needs something like, "That's an area of interest, but you need to do something else first." Would be nice to have a more thought out story line to help with direction. Graphic and mechanics are a little boring. Basically just moving from one still screen to the next.

Really enjoying this game. Clever and intelligent. As a veteran of such games, The Room series, Legacy, all three, (hope there is a fourth on the way), and the Da Vinci series, I know the 'nature of the beast', as it were. I understand the reviewers frustrations about the lack of hints, but it is worth it. Having said that I had to resort to YouTube ,(once so far), after 2 hours play! One comment I do agree with is a map would be a great addition.

I've played all the Myst games, all The Room games, the House of Davinci games, Meridian 157 games, this is THE HARDEST BY FAR for me. Even using online hints I became so frustrated with the game I uninstalled it. I will not buy another one from this maker.

Visually stunning, but very frustrating at points. Some puzzles were very hard, so had to resort to walkthroughs. I would never have got through certain parts without that help. Still, it was enjoyable, but need a break until my next game.

Horrible controls, super touchy. Not compatible with stylus. No hints for what amounts to a HOG with odd puzzles. Screen is much too dark which requires setting brightness on tablet to max resultig in very short battery life for gameplay. Several hellish puzzles (the stone rings painting in particulat) should have a skip option. Just a tedious experience. Not fun.
Awesome
I love the game, graphics were outstanding and storyline was great, except you guys should have showed Michael leaving to go back to his family, and Ben thanks for helping me :-)

Unfortunately either due to a bug or phone incompatible I could not get past the first gate. I contacted the Devs and a solution couldn't be found. They offered me a refund. I would be happy to try this game again should a solution be found for my issue.

Really enjoyed this game. Graphics are beautiful! Great imagination! A little too difficult for a novice gamer like me. Needed better/easier/more hints. Had to revert to a walkthrough ALOT! The very end became so frustrating I didn't even finish the game, thus the four stars. But I do recommend the game.

Good graphics but poor gameplay. I've played it for nearly two and a half hours, completed some puzzles and still have no real idea what I'm supposed to be doing. Also, really frustrating trying to get around without a map, as I kept going round in circles in and out of the same rooms trying to find a particular location. Could also do with some hints as there are times when it is unfathomable what you need to do next. Sorry, but I gave up and uninstalled.

Really enjoyed this game! Excellent graphics, solid navigation, an imaginative story well told, good depth and length, and challenging puzzles. Minimal permissions (thank you, devs). Runs smoothly, glitch-free. Not for beginners: it does demand a fair bit from the player. It helps to be very observant since this game won't hold your hand or baby you (plenty of walkthroughs out there--I used Appunwrapper's).I like to revisit it. Well worth the asking price; Definitely a classic, underrated game.
Great artwork, challenging puzzles, no problems, so many places to go to solve the many puzzles! A map of places explored would be helpful.
Very tricky. Really great challenging puzzles.
It's a good game.
Very good and interesting game
Great game, lots of challenging puzzles and an immersive story line.
Challenging fun!
Wow! So Amazing!
Pretty good game and ending I just want more with the game. And I would like a second game
Just about the only pro to this game is the graphics. It desperately needs hints; the puzzles (especially at the end) are extremely difficult to solve.
Are Game Is Good
Great game. Some puzzles need some taught, some are not too difficult, then there are a few downright tough ones. Love this game. Good for your brain.
Fascinating and original game. Some of the puzzles are difficult and a bit obscure but the haunting storyline and beautiful artwork more than compensate. I was sorry when it ended.

Love the graphics but this game really needs a hint button. Just want to be able to play without having to go to the walkthrough. Information on things I tap on would be good also. Just cannot enjoy this game having to consult walkthrough is not my idea of enjoyment. Way to much money spent for such a game. Sorry guys. Hint button, hint, button, hint button.
Loved the graphics and length.... Tricky but fun
Its very interesting and I wish I could keep playing but I can' t get the dagger to go into the disc on the wall. Very frustrating.
Excellent puzzle game, lots of content for price, some very tricky puzzles.

The game will not install. It downloads fine, but errors out during installation. The game appears on my device, but will not load past the initial splash screen. I will change my rating if this is fixed. I am running Android 10.

I really like this game, except.... The figures that I collected from the ceiling disappeared never showed in my inventory. It is the same with the eclipse painting that I took. So now I suppose I am stuck and have to start over?? Please advise

Overall a really great game. The puzzles varied nicely from easy to hard, and the clues not too obscure. Very impressive for an indy developer and better than many I've played from big name companies. I really liked the additional puzzle solving you can optionally do after completing the main quest, and the disabling of puzzles and clues once you've solved them is something I wish all games would do. I'd definitely purchase another puzzle game from this developer.

Meh... This game would have recieved 5 stars, BUT.... It stopped working after I got to the third chapter. I had to uninstall and then reinstall. After doing so, all my progress had been lost completely. Several hours of gameplay just gone! I'm not pleased, as other games like this tend to save the data and pick up right where you left off. Also, there is no hints at all to what you're supossed to be doing. No clues whatsoever. Very dissappointed.
Awesome game. Great graphics, challenging puzzles, great story.
Needs a hint button.
It won't play just stays on new game page I've uninstalled and installed it but still the same. I've already purchased it and played parts of game and now it won't work .
Game does not start...black screen..used to run perfectly earlier..please help..tried uninstalling and reinstalling on s10 plus

Update: I'm making this 5 stars. Best puzzle game I've posted since The Room. The puzzles become more demanding each step of the way. To solve many of them, you really need to stretch your imagination and thought process. I'm still working on the last level and I've been playing almost every day. I'll be sad when I'm done as I don't know of many other games of this caliber. I hope a sequel is on its way.

There is way too much going on for phone play. Things are difficult to see. You have to tap everywhere just to find what is playable. I like more logic, less hide and seek. A larger device may be a little more enjoyable, buy not sure it would make a difference. The coins and little men are just tedious. I loved The Room series and Davinci. This is ok, but you'll be disappointed if you're expecting/hoping for the same.

Very good classic point and click game. Some puzzles were extremely frustrating, so I really missed a skip button. Other comparable games have one. Then the screen was way too dark, I had to turn brightness level on my tablet to max, but even then some areas were still obscure. Plus this drained the battery insanely fast. Apart from these issues, a very relaxing game you can explore at your leasure, without annoying hidden objects or unnecessary human interactions, just like in good old Myst.

It's definitely a good game. Good graphics and music. Engaging, one ends up caring about what happened to the family that lived there. Would have been 5 stars if it weren't for the glitchy controls when it comes to inserting keys/cylinders etc. It shouldn't take over an hour, quitting the game, or restarting the phone to be able to insert something. Still haven't managed the pivoting art cylinder keys, graphics matched up perfectly, won't insert. Got too frustrated after an hour and moved on!
Ceiling puzzle when done correctly, wont open the bookshelf passageway. Wasted my money.
Brilliant game

Before I got inside the castle, it glitched on the barrels next to the door. I could not get off the screen and ended up having to shut my phone off. I uninstalled it and would really like my money back, but now I can't find the refund button. Please tell me I didn't just waste $5 on this game.

A varied mix of puzzle difficulties, some of them proved quite difficult. Toughest part of the game is finding the active content. It is tedious to have to click on every pixel on the screen just to see whether an action can be performed there. The "highlight content" option does nothing as far as I can tell. Otherwise, the graphics are great and the storyline well scripted.

I have emailed twice now asking for help with no reply. I entered the proper puzzle on the ceiling, just like what's in the book. Even had to peek at a walkthrough to make sure I did it correctly but it wont open the book shelf up..nothings happening. Please tell me I didn't just waste 10 bucks on a game that's flawed.
One of the better games for sure
Hellish game controls, repetitive action, basic solutions, indifferent graphics.
No tips, nothing. Controls are poor. Could have been made better.
Beautiful game. Challenging puzzles, neat story line, incredible graphics.
Excellent game. Comparable to The Room, and Legacy series. Great puzzles and plenty of game-time. Hopefully not the last from this developer.
Won't even open just continuously loads
Amazing
Excellent so far but I'm only on level 1.
Great gameplay, graphics, and challenging puzzles!

Eyes of Ara is a visually pleasing game. The story line keeps the game interesting and eager to see what lays around the next corner. Two issues l have is there is a lot of repeat puzzles. The other thing is finding all the hidden items that really don't add to the game itself. For the price per chapter of game play is a bit pricey but worth not having to deal with annoying ads.
Excellent puzzle game. Surprisingly long and great difficulty.

The game wasn't logical when compared to others, a lot of wandering around to find what to do next. Some u could see connections between puzzles and some puzzles needed exact line ups to make them work, so a lot of fiddling around. Those paintings with specific frames that matched the boxes were ridiculous. I needed the walkthrough for them, maybe because the game was so dark. Not a chance it can be compared to The Room.

Excellent graphics. It is a complex game with many puzzles to solve and clues. Well worth the cost. Some clues and touch points hard to spot due to darkness. I could not have completed game and especially not have met all the achievements (except for Halloween and Merry Holidays special events, which I missed) without AppUnwrapper walkthroughs and one other I found to help with rotating tiles on a stone ceiling.

Very engaging and complex. The art is lovely and detailed and most of the puzzles are challenging but not impossible. Having the option to light up important items makes the general dimness less of a problem. My one dislike is that some puzzles have very specific controls that must be set just so, but the actual control is not precise enough (the ossiloscope took nearly 15 minutes to set, not because i didnt know the setting, but because the dials delayed and overshot.)
Awesome game, had to look really close for stuff. Great graphics!
Terrible! Was unable to play because control went from hypersensitive and flying all around the view, slow and lagging or totally unresponsive. Asked for a refund.

The controls are clunky, however the game and the plot are fabulous, there are secrets within secrets within secrets, layers and layers of puzzles and enough gameplay to last one a week. I typically get through one of the Room games in a couple of hours tops, this one was really much tougher in comparison. The graphics and the controls are definitely not on the same level as the Room series, but the intricacy of the puzzles is unmatched by anything else I've played so far on Android!

Good game. Great graphics and game play. Loved the story, too. Some of the puzzles were beyond me, couldn't have made it without a walkthrough. By the epilogue, I gave in. Reminded me too much of college calc. No fun.
Disappointing
Difficult! Good game but couldn't complete it without a walkthrough as some of the puzzles are quite tricky

Excellent value! Well-rendered graphics and puzzles are natural extensions of the world. Some of the clues are a bit unclear, especially near the end, but most made good logical sense. I got over 12 hours of very enjoyable gameplay from this purchase.
Game was fun but the controls were difficult
Omg.horrible.no real hints or skips.wasted my money.totally frustrating.
Great game!

I've not played for long yet, but it's looking good so far! One thing, would it be too hard to bind the 'back' button to the 'zoom out' function? Then I (and others) would be able to play on my TV (right-click on mouse binds to 'back') cheers!

Some good puzzles to appreciate, but a lot less logical than other similar games. A few necessary parts of the game are far too hidden and area is too large to keep moving between rooms. Don't understand how the comments can say this is in the same league as The Room Series

This game is very good. It got extremely complicated once I got to the Planetarium. Nothing more after that made any sense, I had to use a walkthrough on YouTube. But please get rid of the circular puzzle near the water. Or just changed the way it can be solved. Multiple pieces moving at the same time makes it extremely complicated to complete a puzzle. I've been working on this puzzle far too long. Other words it is a great game, amazing graphics and pleasant music. Thanks to the Developers.

Though I was able to make it quite a way through on my own, much of it requires walkthroughs. Some objects are way too difficult to see due to dark graphics. Must be played in a dark environment and then it is still difficult to locate some objects. Entertaining otherwise.
Doesn't load on OnePlus 6 (android 10, oxygen os 10.3 - build A6003_22_191214)
Love it!
Boring gameplay, cluncky controls
Difficult, but very enjoyable. Needed app unwrapper a lot! Fans of The Room should like this.

A great game worth the money in time and effort. Great graphics and game play. Finding various items can be tedious. Some puzzles, in my option, are unsolvable without online walk through. Brick wall is one. Creating the energy orb has no completion indicator. What's the lever socket in subterranean room off the first floor study for? I will buy more of your games at this quality.
If you like real adventure games, this one is for you. The game just keeps on giving. It's worth every penny and more.
Bought it. Started the game. At main menu and clicks wouldn't register on anything, so couldn't even play. Refunded. Galaxy S9+.

Awesome story very immersive and challenging puzzlles. Would give 5 stars but theres still some glitches. Found the 1/1 artwork and it only says ive acquired it if im in the location i found it. I did get it on sale, but for spending some monet for a game i would hope these issues can be addressed and fixed. Overall great job awesome and beautiful game! Edit: i see now that there's new collectables in different areas. Interesting! Glad to see its potentially a longer game !!

Ok, call me Mr Picky if you like, but when I pay for a game I expect a little more than a flash of the company's title card and twenty minutes of a black screen, especially when there is no indication the game may be incompatible. Not having played it I can't comment other than to say it looks good and I'm sorry I never got a chance to play. I'll take my refund with a clear conscience.
Paid for this game and it will not load after opening. Sad, really wanted to play üòï

Good mind blowing game for all fans of The Room or House Of Davinci fans. I would rate it 5 star, if the game had hints or built-in help: starting from some point the riddles are so sophisticated that is almost impossible to pass them.
I love this game a little hard but great
Wonderfully immersive game good value too...great graphics and game play is ok. The only gripe I have is that the clues are vague and spread over too many rooms.
Love it, but am stuck. Even after watching a cheat, I can't make the knife insert into the clock.
Great puzzles s and gorgeous graphics. I wish I could inspect them closer!

I have given 5 stars because the graphics are excellent and the game works fine. Everything is there to solve the puzzles, but if you get stuck there is unfortunately no hint system to nudge you as to your next move. Also there is a lack of a map, so at times I have found it hard going remembering what is where and wasted time looking. All in all if you are used to this type of game I am sure you will like it very much.
One of the best in this genre I've played. Grunted through on a small screen without looking at any walkthroughs or cheat codes and probably had over 30 hours on it. Great job dev.
Great game I loved it.
Sad excuse for the Room
Bugs. After solving the ceiling puzzle, the book case didn't open. After finding all the 3 paintings, i couldn't put the paintings in the frame. The game didn't allow me to. Waste of my money.

Unfortunately had to refund. Got inside castle, found an odd thing w 3 designs that spun & all that happened was "try interacting with your item". Well, really? No true hints, the pic of the device in the book is lol blank & can't even select the blanks, the markings on the generator do not conform to any selections in the device. I had to give up before I lost $5 to a game I could only play 10 min of. Shame. Seems an incredible game til then. Maybe if i find a walkthru I'll DEF rebuy this.

The game has good graphics and the puzzles are well enough, maybe a bit on the easy side. The story line is a bit too far and in between for me though, leaving the game a little boring. Also, a map feature would be great, because it's kind of a pain to remember which door goes where. Overall, not really my type of game.
Fun game. Difficult enough to keep it interesting!!
Excellent game!!! Great graphics, puzzles are insane!!

It's the game that keeps on giving. Hours of game play especially if you want to hunt out all the hidden extras that make the game more fun. It's quite challenging. I had to resort to the walk through quite a few times but only after having a good go at it first myself. It doesn't ruin the game as long as you just stop the video as soon as you find out something useful and carry on as long as you can before getting stuck again. Just don't give up! There's so much more to discover üòé
Every time I made a move to read, touch, grab, or whatever, the game would lock up and I would have to exit the game to reset. Good luck with that.2
Futility brought to Droid
Love it. Lots of fun. Challenging. Great graphics. Remanicent of myst
Beautiful, challenging, rewarding
I loved the entire castle! Puzzles were great. Graphics AMAZING. So good!! More, please!
Very solid puzzle game. The first half is fantastic, 5 star quality. The second half requires a lot of big logic leaps and becomes a bit frustrating.
Didn't work on my Android phone. Not playable at all. Don't fall for this like I did. Now I'm out money.
Loved it
Tricky, and makes you feel a bit seasick! Could do with a map, I can't remember what is where.
Absolutely brilliant so sad lve finished it loved every second üíúüíúüíúüíú
Huge fan of the Room and Da Vinci and this is just a good as them. So impressed with everything in this game.
So much fun makes me think of the old PC game MYST.
Amazing!
It looks like a good game and all but how are you not going to have hints available? When you get stuck there is no way of getting help and that makes it no fun to play cause you cant go any further.
Just boring.
Fun and challenging game , good story..
Brilliant game! I enjoyed the challenges and the graphics were excellent.

This game is awesome. I love the Room games, and this is better because it is more challenging. The graphics are amazing, the puzzles are good and the rooms of the castle seem endless. I have used 2 hints online so far from a hint site (lots of those exist), if you need that use it but enjoy the challenge. People who are hating on this game clearly just haven't taken the time to think, because often the solutions can be pretty clear, it just may take time to get there. Highly recommend
Great story line, challenging puzzles, lots of secrets to find.
Was an amazing game untill it got so hard to play just devastating. Please reconsider for future games.

This game is great, it is not a simple one. What Im not fun of, is that it requires too much clicking to not to miss active zones, artifacts and etc. But the puzzles, atmosphere and everything else is brilliant. And I see why some rated it with one star, yes it is frustrating to realize you don't have enough brains to beat the game. And please don't mention the rooms series, this one is different!
Great graphics and good puzzles which can be tricky to find and solve

UPDATE. The silly, totally unnecessary and tacky special Halloween graphics and themes completely takes me out of the games great atmosphere and completely ruined it. Why the F..k do devs do this? I paid for this game and you have corrupted it. What can I say? Devs need to make more experiences like this for android. The Room, The House of Davinci, Returner 77, all get it right. The Eyes of Ara is no exception. Keep em coming.

Just beginning and like both the visuals and puzzles so far, but having an issue playing it on my Samsung Galaxy Tab S3. Screen frequently freezes, can't look around, can't zoom in. Have to shut it down, wait, and resume later. But it then happens again after only 4 or 5 moves. Very frustrating. Fiddled with settings, didn't help. Anyone have a suggestion?
Pretty decent puzzle game. Some aren't intuitive, but was really fun to play through.

Love this game reminds me of "the room" trilogy & davinci game. Wish more developers would make games like this..PLEASE MAKE MORE!!!! ... only gripe is it needs a fast travel map..takes too long to move from place to place espically moving between chapters... also a note.. make the rooms a bit lighter in color, very hard to see unless it's dark and screen brightness is all the way max(which is why 4‚òÜ Instead of 5‚òÜ...OH AND YES NEED USE OF SPEN!!!!
Immersive, beautiful world; compelling, satisfying puzzles; engaging story. Great attention to detail that a curious player will find rewarding again & again.
Not easy,challenging,awesome game.
Thank you
I really loved this game. It's very similar to the Room series but you definitely need a cheater here and there as some of the puzzles are not intuitive. Overall, it was a ton of fun.
Terrific game! Controls were effortlessly. The rooms were just beautiful couldn't wait to enter each one. Made it so you enjoyed having to be though in your search of clues.
Awesome
Very good graphics but clues can be a bit vague and hard to find apart from that not bad

This is an amazing game. It is also a very challenging game. The decision to not include a hint system makes this game unique among it's peers, and in my opinion, it is much better without one. It makes solving the puzzles much more satisfying. The graphics are extremely detailed, enabling much more nuanced puzzles.
Awesome game
Game won't let me click anywhere - unplayable
Awesome game!
Played it on the big screen,just as awesome on the smartphone.
Absolutely incredible. The planetarium section should get an award just by itself.

Great game. Take good notes but if not appunwrapper. Can't wait for the next game. I am a huge Myst fan and this game is in that style but a couple of puzzles are quite challanging but still fun. Played for 22 hours over two weekend so worth the cost.
It's okay. Not great. I decided to refund. If price was lower ($3-4 range), I would have kept it and played on.

I crave these types of games yet the good ones like this are a rarity I've replayed this game 5 times and still enjoyed each time but as things go once you've memorized every aspect of it it's time to move on to another.. ive played most of the similar games all of the rooms series and house of davinci ..just wish there was more of this type and quality out there I gave it 5 stars because I totally loved it ..Please!! Developers Make more Games like These. üòÉ
A very challenging and enjoyable puzzle game! Very well done!
Best game I've played this year. Excellent on all aspects. I want more like this!

Struggled with puzzles. Used the walkthru alot. I love games like this. 3D, intricate and amazing graphics. Unfortunately l gave up at atop the castle. 2nd puzzle "134" numbers. I couldn't get it done. Gave up. Uninstalled unfinished... looked at walkthru for ending... beautiful
Fun.
Makes u use brain
Incredible through the first 2/3 of the game, but then the puzzles became ridiculously obscure. Watched the last 1/3 on YouTube. Ending was pretty weak.

Playing the game on Samsung Tab S3 and it plays very well, however, i would love the option of using my spen. Double tap to back out or in, move with pen. Can this not be an option? Music, graphics, and overall presentation is great. A little dark in areas so playing in a darker room and not in very bright room would be recommended.
Awesome game!
when I started the game It looked cool. But when I tapped the first area, I got stuck , I cannot back up, any Ideas.

This is an amazing game, beutiful graphics, great sounds, so well made, but, and its a big but, its so difficult, i have never found any game this hard, am now on 7 hours playing time, and without appunwrapper, then i would have stopped and deleted it. Its a pity that its so hard, but thank god for evternal help!! So only 3 stars.
An amazing game if you like complex puzzles

Edit. I've managed to find out the issue (without any help, but this is a one man band though you expect to get support for the cost).
